This repository contains the presentation and the grammar files from a tutorial on using the LinGO Grammar Matrix for the implementation of HPSG grammars: 

http://arademaker.github.io/blog/2021/04/05/grammar-matrix.html

To create the LKB files of a grammar, visit the LinGO Grammar Matrix customization system:



https://matrix.ling.washington.edu/customize/



Then upload a choices file by clicking on "Choose file" and "Create Grammar" at the botton of the page.
To the test the created grammar, run the script in the lkb folder with the LKB system (menu option LKB/Load/Complete grammar). Parse the test_sentences file to check which sentences the grammars parses.  
